replies.body:
The only thing I want for her is getting a buff on her mana cost (w and e are pretty high with both costing 110 mana at rank 5) after all the nerfs and changes she got. She was buffed too fast after her release, then her W-Cast got changed (despite the fact that the previous cast was better) and then she got several nerfs but no compensation buff. 

Ps: I play Taliyah with: {{item:3020}} {{item:3116}} {{item:3027}} {{item:3151}} {{item:3001}} {{item:3157}}  
This build has quite a lot of mana because of rod but it still often feels like her costs are too high. The build has less damage than a build with void staff or another dmg item but I like it because of a good mix on utility/survivability and damage (flat magic penetration from boots and liandrys -> which gives extra damage based on the hp of the enemy).
